snippet.textDisplay:
Tbh I'm not surprised people are comparing Matt to Avi. The moment I heard Avi had left, I always assumed every video with the new guy (whose name I just learnt by skimming the comment section) would get a lot of criticism. It is HARD to replace a long-standing member or introduce a new one into any long-established group (even in fiction) without having lots of people be salty about it.


 That said, this is the first video I've watched with Matt and I've gotta say, I really enjoy hearing him mercilessly roast the Grinch.

snippet.textDisplay: i think it’s so disrespectful to say that matt is not talented enough and that they want avi back. not only is that disrespectful to matt, it’s also disrespectful to the whole group and avi as well. avi wanted a different life. he wasn’t happy. yes, avi is a phenomenal bass but he has a different timbre than matt. no one is going to be able to sing like avi and no one is going to be able to sing like matt. personally, i believe matt is EXTREMELY talented and i’m happy he’s finally been showcased. can we talk about that range? i can’t imagine what it’s like for him to be constantly told by his “fans” that they want avi back and that matt will never live up to the expectations. no one likes to hear that. matt is a good bass, he’s solid. change sucks, but this is good change.
